title: Mix Circles Podcast
description:
Welcome to the Mix Circles Podcast. Here, I and those who appear on this podcast throw all titles, all skin colour, everything away, and focus on the least focused on part of life; Genuine conversation. Like the groups of older generations meeting at your local coffee shop, having a calm debate between two humans of different backgrounds… different upbringings… different perspectives. 
Now, for me “Mix”, I’m just an idiot, only trying to make it through life, one day better then the last one, one day at a time. I’m a Millennial, not by choice, but because I’m swept into that pile. I come from a cadet background (Royal Canadian Air Cadets), and I DO NOT back down to those who challenge my views/beliefs. BUT, I am just a licensed bodyman from Canada, with possibly some mental disconnections. Honestly, just a nobody that has surprised himself as to how he has gotten this far in his life, when people used to tell him the cliché terms like you’re “no good”, “worthless”, “stupid”, “weirdo”; that you’re just stupid and will not succeed. Battling himself, trying to find the “meaning of life”. If you’re like me, you often find yourself alone, asking. ”What is the correct way to think/interact? Why are humans here? How did we come to be? What is the REAL TRUTH? Is it Science, Is it Religion? Where are we going? Who will lead us? Who will lead us humans to greatness? But, aren’t we all just that? Human. So why not come along for the ride, be human, come join my discussion circle, have a coffee or tea, and let’s talk; Shall we?
Some of you, are probably asking, but WHO is this guy? For privacy reasons, I wish for my identity to stay private. I do not wish for fame. YES I DO NOT WISH FOR FAME. I don’t wish to be worldwide know. I just want people to LISTEN TO THE PODCAST. I am merely just using this platform as all AMAZING podcasters do (on this amazing service), Just as a meeting point, to discuss views and have a good discussion, to take a step back from life (stop to smell the roses), just relax, have a conversation about whatever comes to mind and not have to worry about "Nae-Sayers". Focus on genuine conversation between two humans.

title: Wylde Style Network
description: After a looonnnggg hiatus, Wylde Style Radio “Unreal Radio” is BACK and has their own Network now! Featuring Stand Up & Shout, Notebook Wagering, Tribe Called Jess, Welcome to Manassas (A Classy Variety Show) and more WYLDE shows to come, WSN will bring the fun back to our “unreal" network…also known as streaming and/or podcasting. We will also be looking to add other fun shows to add to the Wylde Style Network. Contact us if you think you’ve got what it takes to be a show on the Wylde Style Network. Wylde Style Radio got started in 2007 as an add-on to the Wylde Style brand when owner, Jeff Wylde, got together with his good friends Kevin Shafer and Rocky Parrish to form Wylde Style Radio w/ Kevin & Rock. The goal was to get the show on terrestrial radio as “Guy Talk” was what was hot at the time. The problem was, they had no idea how to do that other than trying to work connections and put a demo together. So, after working all their contacts and bringing on AV expert, John Caniford, to try something new at the time called live streaming and podcasting, Wylde Style Radio w/ Kevin & Rock launched it’s first show from studios they built inside of the now defunct Chics-N-Wings. The show was a pioneer in podcasting and streaming as even the major stations hadn’t started doing it at the time. The show was instantly popular but a little to bawdy for management at Chics-N-Wings so they had to rethink their strategy and decided to take the show on the road…in a pink RV. At that time Wylde Style Productions had a pink “party bus” RV for its events. WSR moved into the “Pink Nightmare” and we took the show to the masses, doing live shows from outside of popular local bars and businesses like Hooters, The Rhino, PJ Skiddoos, Good Times Tattoos and more. WSR continued to build their audience until 2009 when Kevin & Rock got the call up to the big leagues, 106.7 The Fan DC. They continued to do their show on various platforms until 2016 when everyone went their separate ways until now, when we decided to “get the band back together” as they say. Now we've evolved into our own network with other "Wylde" shows to boot!

Overall, "Boomer Dad Millennial Comrades" provides a space for critical analysis and discussion of political and social issues from a socialist perspective. The hosts strive to challenge conventional ideas and inspire listeners to engage in meaningful political action.

"Needeepinbeanz" is a captivating and lighthearted podcast that takes listeners on a delightful journey through the world of beans and beyond. With its unique blend of humor, curiosity, and exploration, this podcast is a perfect escape for those seeking both entertainment and education.

Hosted by a charismatic group of bean enthusiasts, the podcast dives deep into the diverse universe of beans – from the humble kidney bean to the exotic black-eyed pea. The hosts' infectious laughter and genuine enthusiasm for the subject matter make even the most mundane bean variety seem fascinating and exciting. Listeners will find themselves chuckling along as the hosts share quirky bean facts, engage in spirited debates about the best bean dishes, and even create bean-related challenges that test their culinary skills.

But "Needeepinbeanz" doesn't stop at beans – it's a treasure trove of random ideas and passionate discussions that span a wide range of topics. From dissecting the science behind the perfect cup of coffee to exploring conspiracy theories about ancient civilizations' connections to beans, every episode brings something new to the table. The hosts' boundless curiosity leads them to tackle subjects as diverse as astrophysics, underwater basket weaving, and the cultural significance of sock colors.

Listeners are in for a treat as they become immersed in the hosts' infectious enthusiasm for their passions. Whether they're embarking on a whimsical quest to discover the world's largest baked bean or engaging in a friendly debate about the merits of jelly beans versus chocolate-covered coffee beans, the hosts' chemistry and camaraderie make each episode a joy to listen to.

What sets "Needeepinbeanz" apart is its ability to find the humor and absurdity in the most unexpected places. The hosts' witty banter and clever commentary keep listeners engaged and entertained, even when delving into more serious topics. The podcast seamlessly transitions from lighthearted laughter to thought-provoking discussions, creating a dynamic listening experience that appeals to a wide audience.

With its charismatic hosts, eclectic array of topics, and a dash of bean-inspired charm, "Needeepinbeanz" offers a refreshing and hilarious take on podcasting. It's a podcast that celebrates the joy of learning, encourages embracing one's passions, and reminds us all to find humor in the everyday – even if that means taking a deep dive into the world of beans. So, whether you're a bean aficionado, a casual listener, or someone simply looking for a good laugh, "Needeepinbeanz" promises to be a podcast that leaves you both entertained and enlightened.
